We recommended that the:

a) Municipal Budget Officer maintain the required registries to prevent the incurrence of expenditures in excess of allotments. Expenditures should be limited to what is appropriated;

b) Municipal Budget Officer carefully review the actual needs of each department of the Municipality so as to properly allocate them in the budget;

c) Agency limits the amount of expenditures as planned to avoid incurrence of expenses in excess of appropriation and so as not to use the funds intended for other projects/activities;

d) Agency prepares an Annual Procurement Program which would serve as basis and control for their procurement activities for the year.

We have recommended that the Municipal Accountant –
 Analyze the transaction and adjust accordingly the books of available documents. Require the Municipal Agriculture Office to submit the acknowledgement receipt to support the dropping from the books of accounts; 
 Provide adequate disclosure on biological assets in the Notes to Financial Statements, such as, but not limited to the following: (a) basis of measurement or value recorded in the books; (b) description of the biological assets, and (c) the program under which such biological assets were purchased and its purpose; 
 Maintain Ledger Card for the Breeding Stock; and 
 Coordinate with the Municipal Agriculture Office for dispersal program under their office, and require submission of duly accomplished acknowledgement receipt for proper accounting of animals in the books. 
Also, we have also recommended that the Municipal Agriculturist / Office of the Municipal Agriculture -
 Coordinate with the Municipal Accountant and submit status report and duly accomplished acknowledgement receipt on the dispersal program of their office; 
 Maintain Livestock Card for each type of large cattle and other bovines acquired by purchase or raised, as well as for small animals including fowls, as provided for under the Handbook on Property and Supply and Management System; and 
 Reconcile their records with the Office of the Municipal Accountant to determine differences and to inform her of raised animals which already reached marketable age or ready for use

We have recommended that management:
 liquidate the unexpended fund transfer; 
 request through a letter to Source Agency to transfer the unexpended balance to the General Fund, duly approved by the source Agency, if the disposition thereof has not been provided in the MOA, Trust Agreement of Memorandum of Understanding; 
 return to the national treasury the unspent balance of ₱23,966,002.29 so that these can be appropriated for more important and urgent programs and projects of the government.

