We recommended that the Acting Municipal Treasurer:
 prepare the Abstract of Collections daily;
 prepare the Consolidated Report of Accountability for Accountable
Forms Monthly;
 submit the RAAF for February 2018 and RCD and RAF for October
16-30, 2018(if any);
 reflect deposits made in the RCD and attach the corresponding deposit
slips;
 require the Accountable Officer sign the RCD;
 ensure that all Accountable Forms received and issued for the month
are included in the RAAF and RCD.

We recommended that management ensure that the LDRRMF, specifically
the 70% mitigation fund be used to support disaster risk management
programs and activities;

We have recommended that the Municipal Accountant and Acting Municipal Treasurer:
 ensure prompt remittance of mandatory obligations in order to avoid incurrence of penalties and to assure that employees can avail of benefits being granted by GSIS; 
 coordinate with the GSIS so that the amount withheld should be the exact amount remitted; 
 identify the concerned employees whom over deductions were made and refund the same; and 
 submit the payroll on salaries and wages of employees for the year 2018

